  <apex:pageBlock title="GuideLines">
  
      <apex:pageBlock title="How to fill, group and count: Details tab" >
          * The first step is to determine a unique 'Project Name' for each of the initiatives. This will enable us to group the initiatives based on 'Project Name'. 
              Use Data--> Group/ Ungroup/ Subtotal functionality in MS Excel to achieve subtotal of each unique 'Project Name'<br/>          
          * Subtotal must be done based on 'Project Name' and the subtotal must be displayed in the 'Project Description' column  <br/>        
          * Primary filter will be applied on the column 'Project Name'. Hence, it is imperative to determine and group the initiatives in broad buckets      <br/>    
          * Once the grouping and counting is done, fields like 'Project Categories', 'Funnel stage', 'Project Lead',  'Landscape', 'Benefit Type', 'RAG status' and 
             'Target Completion dates' must be populated manually, based on the cummulative analysis of the initiatives grouped under the broader bucket. 
              For eg: RAG status of the broader project bucket is green if all the underlying initiatives are green.
      </apex:pageBlock>
      
      <apex:pageBlock title="Dashboard tab">
          * Information from details tab must be reflected in Dashboard tab         
      </apex:pageBlock>
      
      <apex:pageBlock title="Summary tab">
          * Information from Dashboard tab must be reflected in Summary tab.       <br/>     
          * Benefit type must be reflected in Summary tab to enable a high level view of the benefit details         
      </apex:pageBlock>
      
      <apex:pageBlock title="Other guidelines: ">
          * 'Project Name' should be kept minimal, to enable effective grouping <br/>        
          * 'Project Description' contains a short summary of the project             <br/>
          * 'Project Categories' are hard-coded with values mentioned in the table below      <br/>    
          * 'Capability and Launch dates' details is mandatory. If the project is in Feasability stage, then dates must be provided.  <br/>        
          * For RAG status that shows amber or red, explanation and mitigation actions must be provided. Status should be updated every week         <br/> 
          * The tab 'Summary' shows the projects' movement throught the project phases in each of the SME areas           <br/>
          * Once the grouping is done, mention the overall landscape spread for each project          <br/>
          * Cost to implement, for Capacity and Launch - IT cost vs. Non-IT cost  
      </apex:pageBlock>
